    <item>
      <title>A Toothy Grin</title>
      <author> Hairsix </author>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/2420303/a-toothy-grin/</link>
      <comments>https://www.scribblehub.com/read/2420303-a-toothy-grin/chapter/2420328/#comments</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">a820dea5e068241b4c58d44f6bfe6227500dbf53</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 30 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;A down on their luck loser finally lands a job. They quickly find out however, it's not going to be easy. At least the pay is good, right?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;-&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;My first time actually trying to write. I'm heavily inspired by both tales from the gas station and Katalepsis. The main character is a trans woman, and at least one other character will be trans/nonbinary.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/2420303-a-toothy-grin/chapter/2420328/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;1. The first day.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;Bzzzzt&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;Bzzzzt&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;Bzzz&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;-&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I cut off my alarm with a slam directed at my alarm's general direction. Laying there, I look up at my ceiling, wishing I could stay there. Knowing better however, I promptly roll out of bed and onto my feet. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Approaching my bathroom, I turn on the sink and splash my face with some water, trying to wake myself up. I make the same mistake as usual and look into the mirror, frowning back at me is the same dishevelled face as always. Brown shaggy hair, dead green eyes with plentiful bags under them. A slight hint of facial hair that I remove daily, and a notable frown. My pale skin certainly didn't make me look any more appealing.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"C'mon, smile. You've got a new job, ain't that cause for celebration? No? Yeah, you're probably right. Just another job that'll fire you in a few weeks for, as they said last time 'bringing down the mood'. Sigh... Fuck..."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Knowing I have better things to do than insult myself, I finish getting ready. After trudging through my morning routine, I grab my keys, and head out of my cramped apartment. After getting down the stairs, I head towards my car, getting ready to head to my first day on the job. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;After checking the email for the location, I type it into my phone and began driving. As I was on my way I started to let my mind wander to how strange the whole thing was. I'd been unemployed for about 4 months now and was chewing through my savings, barreling towards being homeless. While scraping the bottom of the barrel of postings, I saw one for a gas station out at the edge of town.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The application process was strange to say the least. They only asked for my name, number, email, and how comfortable I was being alone over night. I absent mindedly filled it all out and moved on, not expecting much. Not even an hour later, I got an email. I checked it and paused with disbelief. I was immediately responded to. There was no interview or background check. All that was listed was the address, and that I would be starting in two days. It's safe to say I was wary, but I didn't have too much of a choice. So as I headed towards the gas station I silently hoped I wouldn't just end up getting robbed when I got there.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;When I finally pulled up, I was at a loss, just taking in the scene in front of me. There was two people standing outside, both gathered either side of some slab of flesh on the ground, about the size of a golf cart. As I pulled up and parked, the one on the left, a punk looking girl with piercings waved me over.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Hey! You're the new guy! My name's Chloe and this is Yale!" She yelled at me from across the parking lot as I slowly crept over. Eyeing the mess of flesh on the ground warily.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"I'm uh... I don't... Okay, what the fuck is that?" I asked, addressing the elephant in the room.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Oh!" Replied Chloe, who was way too eager to explain for my liking. "That's what we're trying to figure out!"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
