      <title>Princess Complex in Another World: Birth of an Aspiring Villlainess</title>
      <author> AmateurAirfryer </author>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/2404115/princess-complex-in-another-world-birth-of-an-aspiring-villlainess/</link>
      <comments>https://www.scribblehub.com/read/2404115-princess-complex-in-another-world-birth-of-an-aspiring-villlainess/chapter/2404124/#comments</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">3953792c3a087fc84493a1c9f9fd61a8d6a93021</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 20 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;After a somewhat delusional young boy meets an untimely end, he finds himself in a room with a Goddess. A Goddess who seems to know more than she lets on. Before he can protest, she shoves the orders of reincarnation down his throat and sends him on his not so merry way.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She did not mention that instead of a hero summoned to defeat a demon king, he (now she), has actually been reincarnation as a princess and future queen of the land. As in female.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Join Lady Anastasia as she reaches the bounds of her new world, refusing to conform to normalcy as she lets her delusions run free, determined to become the most infamous ruler ever known. All the while, the local Prince is trying to rein in his unruly fiancé.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She must discover the secret of who she really is, who her past life was, and why the Goddess picked her of all people to save this world that doesn’t seem to need all that much saving. Most importantly, she needs to learn whether she can face reality, or if she’ll be doomed to live in rose tinted glasses forever.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/2404115-princess-complex-in-another-world-birth-of-an-aspiring-villlainess/chapter/2404124/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;The Secretive Goddess&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p style="font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div class="sp-wrap sp-wrap-default"&gt; &lt;div class="sp-head" title="Expand"&gt; Spoiler &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="sp-body folded"&gt; &lt;div class="spdiv"&gt;[collapse]&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;             &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Steps echo, a cacophony of noise buffeting my senses, trying to snap me out of my focus. Hundreds, maybe thousands, of people walking all around at any given moment, an equal number of eyes looking upon me.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span class="Apple-tab-span"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;            &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;A slight tingling in the back of my eyes commands that I stop, that I turn back, but I refuse. Being a leader is about making hard choices. Being an adult is about letting go. Being me, is to be greater than both.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span class="Apple-tab-span"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;            &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The concrete underneath me is unstable, and cracked with time. Once stark black faded into a dusty grey, reflecting the sun into my eyes. Every few seconds I almost trip in a pothole, perpetually unaware of my next step. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span class="Apple-tab-span"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;            &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;I chide myself as well as I can given the circumstances. A leader should be looking ten steps ahead. They can’t get caught up in… stupid stuff. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span class="Apple-tab-span"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;            &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;I vaguely hear voices in the background. A select few reach my ears despite the chatter of pedestrians and engines of cars. Even above the thundering steps all around me, cutting straight to my heart and bouncing around in my head.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span class="Apple-tab-span"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;           A few of the words are harsh. They do not wish to follow me. They respect my wishes and figure they will just let me be. Maybe it would be more accurate to say they're too angry to chase. Regardless, these are reasonable words. Words I should appreciate, yet for some reason, cannot find it in my heart to.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Others are kinder. Gentler. Worried. Fleeting. Words I should ignore, for my sake and for theirs. And yet with every exhale, every breath,  every trembling word, I want nothing more than to be more like them. It’s a disgusting thought. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Want.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;That’s my problem. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;A leader doesn’t want. A noble doesn’t want. Those who rule empires and touch the heavens, none of them want. They take. If something is in the way, they move past it. To do anything less was a betrayal of the self. And the self is the most important thing of all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Besides basic necessities like hunger or thirst, I need to remove all basic wants. Mediocrity is built off pretending you're happy with your everyday life. The thought that with just a few tweaks you can achieve happiness.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;If all that was wrong with your life was the lack of a few small things, then that’s not truly what's wrong with your life. It’s an excuse, a way to pretend things can get better. A far off dream that what’s happening isn’t your fault.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;The thought that maybe if you were born a little richer, a little more athletic, a different country, gender, whatever… that you would be ok right now. That by working towards that idealized fantasy of yourself you make, the one who isn’t anything like you, that you can find where you're meant to be in life.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Set sustainable goals for realistic growth.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;What a load of crap. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;I know what's wrong with me. It’s not as simple as feeling disgusted by my own skin or being unable to talk with other people. It’s clear to me now, that for the past months I’ve been blinded. Dragged down to the depths of normalcy by those around me. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;These signs aren’t weaknesses, nor are they indicative of any sort of problem with me. Rather they are the manifestations of a soul clinging to its purpose. A purpose of greatness. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;A greatness that can’t be afforded things like self doubt. If I spent my time considering what it is to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;be&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;, I would lose the time to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;. Questioning oneself, contrary to popular belief, is not the mark of a ruler. It is the mark of a fraud.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Deep in my heart, I know this to be true. It is the only thing I’ve ever known for certain. I am destined for great things, I don’t have time to be bogged down. If something is in my way, I steer clear, and continue on my path to destined glory.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;And yet…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;It’s as if I can’t control myself. My steps begin to grow faster and faster. Am I running? That would make no sense. To run is to give into base animal instincts. To lose all composure. But… I am running.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;The world begins to blur as the populated streets fade slightly, each stride taking me further and further from the people I need to escape. Towards the shadows where I belong. I turn into a dark neighborhood but I do not stop.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;As I run, each passerby feels dangerous, a predator waiting to strike. It’s like their eyes pierce through me, or rather, smother me. Trapping me in my mortal form. I can’t be anything at all, I’m locked in place. Stuck.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;It doesn’t make sense. Why am I acting like this? Not only is it entirely opposite to what I consider to be dignified, but it’s entirely too girly for someone like me to be doing. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;And girly is really the last thing that I am. The last thing I should be at least. At the very least, it is something entirely out of place in a neighborhood like this. It’s not exactly the sort of place where one should wander around out of breath and tired. Especially when there's a serial killer on the loose. I really hope that’s not a poorly set up death flag.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Finding a slightly less grimy alleyway than the ones now surrounding me, I sink to my knees. I shouldn’t care what they think. Not my… companions, and especially not these random people on the street. They shouldn’t matter to me. They don’t matter to me. But I can’t get them out of my head.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;What do they see when they see me? Who do they see? There are two people after all. Or there should be at least. There's the mask, and there's the person. An ugly person. A person who is unloved. Uncared for. And yet, a person who will achieve great things. Who people will have no choice but to look up to, whether in awe or envy. A ruler. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Then there's the mask. It’s unruly and unnatural. Fake. Nothing about it is anything but a means to an end. A way to find out how people talk to one another. A way to be friends with people without risking my own self. Without exposing too much. A way to be secret and present. And yet… it's perfect.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;I feel a trail of wetness down my cheek and wonder when it started raining. Footsteps seem to echo once more, booming down the narrow alley. I don’t look up. I can’t. It would be beneath me for anyone to see me right now.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;It isn’t raining.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;The mask is everything that I am not. It is everything that I loathe. It’s entirely too people pleasing. It cares about others. It is considerate without hope of gaining something in return. It is… pathetic.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;It’s not me. Where the mask can stand boldly in the sun, and feel the smiles of people upon it, I slink into the shadows, watching and waiting. I will stay there until it is my time and I will grow wings, however metaphorical, and blot out the sun. After all, it is in my nature to hurt. From the day I was born, my destiny was set and my rule was prophesied. A great ruler. A terrible ruler. Someone nobody can ignore or forget.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;I snap out of my thoughts just in time to hear a manic giggling above me and then… &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Yikes… that was one &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;awful&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; way to go out, wasn’t it?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Huh? Where am I? Why am I so… calm? I sit in a stark white room, glowing and somehow feeling fancier than I have a right to be in, despite my divine right to rule implying that I have more authority than anyone to be here.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Wow, you’re quite the little narcissist aren’t you? Wouldn’t have guessed that from the mousy little disciple I’ve been watching.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;I look up and see a woman with pale skin and long flowing blond hair. She looked like-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“A goddess? Yes well, I’ll skip right to the chase. You already know what’s going on so I’ll just give you a debrief, sounds good?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Before I can even open my mouth to speak she’s in front of me. I couldn’t even react, she was just there, faster than the blink of an eye. And she had her finger covering my mouth in an extremely patronizing way. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“It’s not condescending if I &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;am&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; superior to you. Now hush, I have so many more people to see. I mean, most don’t even get one on one visits, but you’re a very special case to me.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;Obviously I’m special, if you’re a goddess then surely you can- Hold on, why can’t I talk. I can just think super directly. What the hell?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;I glance down and see that instead of the somewhat unpleasant hands I had been expecting, there's like nothing. Not even a glowy figure vaguely in the shape of a spirit. I’m just not there.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Don’t think about it too hard hon, like I said we’re in a very limited time. Besides, I would think you’re happy for an excuse not to talk.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;What’s that supposed to mean?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“I’m afraid as lovely as a little gals chat would be right now, I am a little busy. Kindly stop interrupting me and allow me to finish this chapter. Of your life of course.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;I’m not sure I like that phrasing. But whatever.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Lovely, now-”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;span class="Apple-tab-span"&gt;	&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;Really love that word don’t you?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Oh hush. Now, I’m going to keep this simple because you already know how this is going to go, correct?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;I have an inkling.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Aren’t you proud that your time as a no life watching pointless television shows was able to prepare you for this?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;I’m suddenly glad for my lack of a body, because even though it would go against everything I stand for, I have the vague suspicion I would have a very faint flush right about now.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“You &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; know I’m a mind reader, correct?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;span class="Apple-tab-span"&gt;	&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;Ugh. I wasn’t like… it was just a pass time. I didn’t have anything else to do. And it was… informational.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“While I find your justifications adorable, I’m afraid I’m going to have to proceed. You get the general gist of this.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;Summoned to a parallel world? Defeat the demon lord and become ruler?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Something along those lines, yes. You will be reborn, there will be magic, there will be tension, and there will be romance.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;Wait, reborn? Those are like the creepiest other world stories ever.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Not quite literally. The best way I can describe it is your soul will be there, but &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;you&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; will be reborn.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;span class="Apple-tab-span"&gt;	&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;That doesn’t make any sense, that's just reincarnation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Exactly. Reincarnated.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;So I died?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Oh… the memories. I’m afraid since we have limited time, I had to place a little mental block on you. I’m afraid this goddess can’t be a therapist until you’ve earned a much more substantial block of my time.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;So why even tell me this? If I won’t remember and I’m just a clean slate with the same soul.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Ah, I didn’t say clean slate. You’ll be reborn anew, and regress to a child, but you will still be the same. Personality wise, you’ll be identical to yourself now, although shrunken a bit.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;Meaning?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Meaning that while in this life you may have been a sweet and mild mannered child, in this new one you’ll be how you are now. Which is to say fussy.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;I-I am not fussy. That’s like… don’t treat me like a child.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“I do hope you realize that to a goddess like me, you are.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;Whatever. Do I at least keep my memories. A super genius or whatever. Bring modern powers of medicine to a disease stricken world?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Wow, that is quite the savior complex you have there, it’s adorable. Don’t let it get to your head.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;Aren’t you on a time limit?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Fine,” she sighs exaggeratedly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“No you will not keep your memories, so kiss those dreams away now. As you grow you will get flashes of who you were, but mostly just the core parts of your identity.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;So, clean slate?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;She sighs again.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“How to best explain this? Hm… suppose that right now you are incomplete.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;Huh?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“You spent the majority of your life hiding. This isn’t passing judgement by the way, it takes most people a significant amount of time to truly discover themselves, and your time was cut rather unnaturally short.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;span class="Apple-tab-span"&gt;	&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;Okay…? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“This new life you're living will give you the opportunity to piece yourself together again. Think of it as the other half you never knew you had. It is the opportunity to complete yourself. Fully. For better or worse.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“You will be born with the vague knowledge that you are a reincarnation, and the personality you developed over your first life. As you grow and begin to mature, you will slowly come to remember and understand this part of your soul.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“So it’s not like a complete rebirth where you are a totally new person, and it’s not like you just get a new body to start from zero with either. When you turn 15 again, you won’t be a 32 year old soul or anything like that. You’ll just be an especially grouchy 15 year old girl with a few extra memories"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;I was not grouchy at 15… wait… did you say girl?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Oh dear, would you look at the time? If this were a story like the ones you watched, I would let you pick a special power, but since it took so long to reconstruct you for our little chat, I just went ahead and did it all for you.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;Wait hold on. You can’t just-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“As for the world you’re going to be sent into, you’ll find it to your liking I hope. Though I must warn you things get very dangerous very fast. I doubt it should be a problem, but given that this is a world that needs saving, you’re going to have to be extra careful. My influence is ever waning, and if it ceases, nothing can protect you.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“By the way, once you turn 17 again, that will be the extent of my abilities. For better or worse, you will be a completed soul, and as such there will be no do overs if you kick it. Unfortunately, I had to pull quite a few strings to get this specific reincarnation, so if you die anytime before 17, the you right now is erased. Clean slate as you said earlier.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-style:italic"&gt;Erased?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-indent:48px;font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;“I suppose what I’m saying is you’ve only got one shot. Don’t blow it, ruler.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="font-style:normal"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
