      <title>The Witch and the Slave</title>
      <author> Shadoobot </author>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/2403447/the-witch-and-the-slave/</link>
      <comments>https://www.scribblehub.com/read/2403447-the-witch-and-the-slave/chapter/2403482/#comments</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">dc75742eec31b8dd190dd7e4508d1296a1184f65</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 20 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;The shock of watching her home burned to the ground almost broke Kiva. Watching her adoptive father die made her feel like her emotions died with him; once burning hot, she struggles to feel anything, good or ill.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The slavers sold her in a market across the ocean. Certain she would be sold to a degenerate noble, Kiva was surprised to find her owner to be a powerful witch. Apparently the witch sees something unusual within her; but as they work together to solve Kiva's true origins, perhaps the master-servant relationship between them might start to change.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;~~~&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Disclaimer: The inspiration for this story came from an AI chatbot scenario. The AI sucked though, so pretty much the entire thing is written by me. I even got a friend to do the proofreading instead of a robot.&lt;br /&gt; The protagonist would probably be considered transgender. Has a woman's body and uses female pronouns, but has male equipment. Not a futanari. Not sure if the Girl's Love tag should be used, but most of the potential romantic interests are women.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/2403447-the-witch-and-the-slave/chapter/2403482/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Chapter 1&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I try to block out the noise.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The noon sun and press of bodies makes the slave market much more hot than most are comfortable with, but I’ve always enjoyed the heat. The smell however, is something I can’t ignore; too many filthy slaves, and the choking perfumes worn by my captors and their potential customers makes me feel light headed. I’m dragged by my shackles, into the back entrance for a large building that only seems to trap the stuffy air. I’m lined up with several other slaves, waiting backstage for our turn to be sold in the auction.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Unlike the starving, low quality slaves advertised and directly sold outside, the ones in here are those the slavers thought could fetch a higher price if wealthy customers are allowed to bid on us. Directly in front of me, is a massive, seven-foot tall man with excessive hair across his entire upper body, displaying his muscles. From the tone of his skin, he likely has some orc blood in him, maybe even ogre. Perhaps he’ll wind up in the pit fights, if he isn’t forced into heavy labor a weaker slave would be incapable of. Right in front of him, a beautiful lady wearing a collar is escorted onto stage. Her role is clear; the slavers obviously spent significant effort dolling her up with makeup and a revealing dress. If she’s lucky, whoever buys her might treat her well, so they can keep her pretty enough to show off to their peers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I try to think about what my own fate will be. When the slavers bought me, they were excited to have another potential pleasure slave- they always sell for high prices, sometimes even higher than the rare trained combat slaves. They pointed out every detail to me when they were inspecting me. My black wavy hair reaches down to just above my waist, perfect for an owner to pull on. My tanned skin, soft and clear, would look beautiful painted white, they said. My clearly hardened body would be able to take any sort of punishment given, yet it’s plush enough to squeeze and hold. My face isn’t as feminine as the slave being bid on now, but I’m told some people like seeing my type break down- that they will want to see my blank expression shatter and my purple eyes widen in shock. I was quickly being given my future role, until the slavers examined my lower body. They were shocked to find out I had a penis instead of a vagina; the bandits never brought it up when they handed me over. They had a hard time deciding if they could even call me a woman at all, since I didn’t even have both sets of genitals like some kinds of Fey supposedly do. Eventually, they decided I’d still be sold in the auction; even if they don’t find some pervert to sell me to, I'm stronger than I look, so I should still get a decent price.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“SOLD!!! To the man with the dashing hat, for four hundred gold!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I’m brought back to the present as the half-orc is sold and escorted off the stage. When he’s clear, I’m directed forwards to stand by the auctioneer. My face remains expressionless as I look over the crowd, wondering who will end up being my owner.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Now, this lovely lady is a real exotic. She comes from across the ocean, as a gift from a savage lord!” I listen as the auctioneer begins his speech, trying to ramp up my price and soften the blow for when he has to reveal my unexpected feature. “Perfect skin, perfect shape, perfect health! Now, I know what you’re all thinking, she’s just another beauty to keep someone’s bed warm. But that’s not all she is! She learns quick, only spent a month with us, before she learned our language. Speaks it better than some natives!” His joke gets some soft laughter from the crowd. “She hasn’t been trained to fight, but she sure can shoot a bow. I personally once saw her pin a falling leaf to the center of a target at eighty yards! She’s strong, too. She’s clearly fit, as you all can see, but packs more punch than any other human her size has any right to. Before we start the bidding, I &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; have to warn you all. They have some strange customs across the water; this lady, isn’t actually much of a lady at all! Instead of the womanly parts one would reasonably expect, she’s equipped like a man; decently sized, too, much to my embarrassment!” He gets a few more laughs despite the surprise, clearly not caring about embarrassing himself for the sake of profits.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Let's get the betting started, making her base price- let’s say, one hundred gold.” As soon as he finishes, several hands go up. As the auctioneer plays the crowd against each other, he gradually increases the price. I observe some of the people betting on me; the first I notice is a  well dressed young man accompanied by an old butler. He keeps his curious eyes on me, like I’m a puzzle to solve. Next, there’s a middle aged woman practically eating me alive with her glances. She was clearly a beauty early in life, but her thick makeup shows a desperation to try and keep the illusion of youth about her. The next person I see is a somewhat heavyset man who has the pleasure slave I saw earlier demurely standing beside him. He’s assessing me with cold eyes, not with lust like the woman, but instead like the slavers. Like he’s wondering how much coin I can earn for him. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Three hundred eighty, for the young master!” At this point, the woman and the brothel owner have dropped out. “Three-eighty, going once! I know your Lord father certainly wouldn’t mind another pretty face around the castle! Going twice!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Five hundred gold.” A woman towards the back suddenly speaks up. She hadn’t bothered to compete in the betting earlier, but now that she has my attention I can clearly see the other guests are subtly keeping their distance. She’s wearing a beautiful, low cut, purple silken dress showing off the incredibly dark tone of her skin. A matching purple hat obscures her face with its wide rim, but her straight white hair can be seen falling down just past her shoulders. Her sudden bet and increase in price causes uncomfortable murmurs to spread. The middle aged woman clearly suppresses a frown, while the young man chuckles and shakes his head.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The auctioneer answers, clearly nervous despite how he should be happy with the jump in profit. “F-five hundred gold, for Lady Thelissa Delvaux! Going once! Going twice!” The crowd is entirely silent as he pauses. “Sold! For five hundred gold!” He quickly waves for an assistant to pull me down off the stage to bring me to my new owner.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I ignore the auction continuing as we approach. Now on even ground, I can better observe her. I’m tall for a woman, but she’s shorter than average; without her hat she’d probably only just reach the bottom of my chin. She tilts her head up to watch us get closer- I catch a startlingly blue eye peek at us from an elegant face. Her perfectly pouty lips are turned up in a slight smile, like she knows she’s completely in control. We stop in front of her, and the assistant holds out the key to my shackles. I can see him hesitate to reach towards her as his hand shakes a bit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“No need for that,” she addresses the assistant. Her voice is soft and rich, but somehow carries well. Too well. It’s like the very air around us demands we hear, and listen to her words. She steps close to me, and reaches a hand up to tug down the collar of my simple shirt. She places her other hand on the center of my chest, above my breasts. “Hold still, dear,” she commands me. For a moment, I feel nothing, but then my body seizes. Her hand burns against my skin. I want to yell from the unexpected pain, but my mouth remains clenched closed. I can feel something radiating out from where she touches me, like vines digging through my body. It thankfully doesn’t last long, leaving me to gasp and try to catch my breath as it ends.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Thelissa pulls back her hands from me and faces the assistant. “Unchain her.” He jumps and scrambles to do as she says. I can see him paler than before the display. Once the chains around my wrist fall to the floor, he crouches down to do the same for the ones around my ankles. I can’t help but rub my wrists, relieved to be rid of the chafing. The assistant manages to undo the last of my restraints, and collects both pieces. A flick of Thelissa’s hand has him hurrying to leave for the safety of the stage.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She looks me up and down a few times, observing what she bought. Seemingly satisfied, she gives me a simple instruction, “Follow me.” She turns her back to me to head for the door; it’s like she doesn’t even entertain the idea of me not obeying. I briefly consider what would happen if I tried to run, but I decide not to take the risk. Not without knowing what she did to me.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;We step outside, and approach a collection of carriages parked in front of the building. She heads to a black carriage with silver lining, in front of which are two equally dark horses. Something feels wrong with them, but it takes me a moment to realise they are completely identical, and standing unnaturally still- not a single muscle twitches. Beside the carriage, stands an aging man with a kindly face dressed in a sharp suit despite the day’s heat. He wordlessly opens the door for Thelissa, who gestures for me to enter with her finger as she steps inside. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Sit,” she orders as she points to the seat opposite her. The man closes the door behind me, leaving me alone with my owner. I barely feel the carriage shift as the man climbs aboard and gets the horses to move us forward. Thelissa shifts her hat upwards to look at me, giving me a clear look at her face. Now with it out of the way, I can see her ears- they’re pointed, and longer than a human’s. I realise she’s a dark elf, and if anything rumored about them is true, then much of everyone’s actions around her become a lot clearer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I am Lady Thelissa Delvaux, and you are to be my new servant. I will explain what I expect from you, but first, tell me about yourself. What is your name? How much of what the slavers said was true?” Cut off from the rest of the world, her voice wraps around me. Even if I hadn’t become a slave, I get the impression I would feel the same compulsion to answer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I keep my voice as flat and emotionless as my face as I answer. “My name is Kiva. I did come from across the ocean, but was never gifted to the slavers by a lord.” I look down to my lap as I continue, trying to not let the faint amount of bitterness I feel show. “I lived in a small village with my adoptive father. It was small enough for everyone there to be practically family. My father taught me how to hunt game, how to use a bow- but I never shot a falling leaf like that. Our lives were simple, but happy, until the bandits came.” I look back up into Thelissa’s eyes, a spark of anger showing through in my own. “I killed the bandit that got my father, but there were too many, and we had no real fighters. They grabbed me as they left; they wanted to rape me for revenge for their comrade. When they discovered I don’t have a pussy, they decided to sell me to the slavers instead, who brought me here.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Thelissa nods at the information. “The brutality of our world often shatters such peaceful lives. Do not bother seeking sympathy for your past while in my service; your purpose will be to serve, and emotions such as that will only get in the way. On that topic, you will always address me as either ‘Mistress’ or ‘my Lady’.” She leans forward in interest. “Now, tell me about your unique biology. Are you sterile, or fully functional? Do you know why your body is like this?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I can feel my cheeks heat up slightly in the change of topic. “I… as far as I can tell, everything works the same as a man’s, down there. I don’t know if I’m virile, since I’ve never… I haven’t been in a relationship. I don’t really know why I’m different, not for sure, but… my father always told me I hatched from an egg. That he found me in an empty cave. He liked to call me his little dragon, but the only proof I was different from normal was being a bit stronger than usual, and my- having a- penis.” I pause before I remember how I’m supposed to address her. “My Lady.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Fascinating.” Thelissa glances over my body again. “If it’s true, that you came from an egg, then you definitely wouldn’t be human. You show practically no cosmetic traits that can identify what you are, except of course the swapped genitalia. I’m going to have to thoroughly examine you, once we get you settled in at my Spire.” She leans back against the seat once the topic returns to something more mundane. “Your duties there are mainly going to revolve around my greenhouse. The plants in there require constant care, and the last servant I had responsible for them passed away several days ago. I also have a small collection of creatures you’ll be looking after.” She gives me a smirk that makes me can’t help but think about how her lips would taste. “I hope you’re capable of handling animals; one of them was responsible for my previous servant’s death, after all.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The thought that the last person in my position &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;died&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; brings me some worry, but it’s not like I haven’t taken care of animals before. Whatever she’s keeping, I can’t imagine them to be more dangerous than the bull my village kept- that thing was &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;savage&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;, not domesticated at all. “I understand… my Lady.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Good. I’d hate to have to punish you so soon for speaking without proper respect.” The mention of punishment reminds me again of my position. “Can you read?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yes, my Lady. The people of my village were actually settlers from this continent, so we mostly spoke this same language. My father thought it would be a good idea for me to learn to write.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Hmph, savage from across the sea, indeed. That man is nearly as much a showman as a slaver.” She reaches for a small book on the seat beside her, having gone unnoticed until now. She hands it to me, which I carefully take to avoid brushing her fingers. “Here’s a collection of instructions for my greenhouse. It details everything growing inside it, and how to care for each plant. Familiarise yourself with its contents as we travel, I expect you to have everything memorized within a moon. Curian, my steward, will help you with your tasks at first, but if a single one of those plants dies there will be consequences. Do you understand?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I nod as I reply. “Yes, my Lady.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I see her turn her head aside from me to look out the window. With the conversation apparently done, I open the book to start reading. As we travel, I occasionally glance up at my owner. She watches as the city goes by, giving way to farmland past its wall. The way her hat shadows her face nearly causes me to stop reading to stare. This scene of her is something I expect would be a fitting painting to decorate a king’s manor. I have no talent for art however, and I’m the only one to see it. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Eventually, the farmland gives way to forest. The light dims, first from the trees, then from the approach of evening.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“We’ve arrived.” Hearing Thelissa speak pulls me away from the book. I glance out the window to see us enter a simple grassy clearing surrounded by a heavy metal fence. “Curian is the one driving the carriage; he will guide you to your room. Once you get cleaned up, he will bring you to the dining room.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yes, my Lady.” We move to a stop, and shortly after Curian opens the door. Thelissa gracefully steps out first. When I exit the carriage, the first thing I see is the structure she’s walking into; a wide building made from completely seamless, dark stone. We’re too close for me to get a good view of its layout, but I can see its center section rise up into a great tower. The roof of the lower section is just as seamless, and made from the same stone- it gently slants up to the sides of the tower. At its very top, I can see a thin claw of black metal sprouting from its side and reaching upwards. The building has no windows, except for a few along the tower closer to the top.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I look back to the carriage when I hear it moving. Curian is still on the ground, standing beside me; seemingly unbothered by the unusual horses moving past the side of the building on their own.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
