      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Cynthia O'Conner is a successful writer. She's written thrillers, horror, fantasy and even a couple of sci-fi novels; her readers never know what to expect from her next book. Romance, however, is something she's never really explored in her writing,. Cynthia has her reasons, but she chooses to keep them to herself.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Richard Walker is an up and coming civil rights attorney. He's dedicated his practice to defend those who are most at risk in an often uncaring society. Those who know him would describe him as a workaholic, only taking time off when he is forced to by his superiors. Because when his lawyer brain becomes idle, it is quickly filled by regrets from his youth. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;A blind-date, set up by each other's friends, leads to an encounter between the two. However, this isn't a story of love at first-sight; it is instead, a reunion. Cynthia had hoped to never see him again, and Richard, for his part, would never have agreed to the date had he known that she was the same person he had hurt all those years ago.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Cynthia promised herself to never forget, but can she forgive? Does Richard even want forgiveness? This a story about scars, both those we inflict on others, and those we inflict on ourselves.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
